<subSubSection id="08F0F8BAFFF6D11DFF39F9FACE0FCBA5" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="4055AB31FFF6D11DFF39F9FACE0FCBA5" blockId="4.[136,1452,1574,2069]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">
<emphasis id="729E7723FFF6D11DFF39F9FACB0FCB6D" bold="true" box="[136,261,1574,1600]" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
─The reflexed posterior petals and protruding stamens are similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="87EAD0B2FFF6D11DFB2DF9FBCF57CB6D" authorityName="E. M. Marais" authorityYear="1997" box="[1180,1373,1574,1600]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Pelargonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reflexipetalum">
<emphasis id="729E7723FFF6D11DFB2DF9FBCF57CB6D" box="[1180,1373,1574,1600]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">P. reflexipetalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but 
<taxonomicName id="87EAD0B2FFF6D11DFA26F9FBCB15CB49" authorityName="E. M. Marais" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Pelargonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="roseopetalum">
<emphasis id="729E7723FFF6D11DFA26F9FBCB15CB49" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">P. roseopetalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the pale pink to almost white flowers and prostrate simple to ternate leaves. 
<taxonomicName id="87EAD0B2FFF6D11DFB5EF997CFA6CB49" authorityName="E. M. Marais" authorityYear="1997" box="[1263,1452,1610,1636]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Geraniaceae" genus="Pelargonium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Geraniales" pageId="4" pageNumber="96" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="reflexipetalum">
<emphasis id="729E7723FFF6D11DFB5EF997CFA6CB49" box="[1263,1452,1610,1636]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="96">P. reflexipetalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has bright pink flowers and prostrate to erect pinnatisect to bipinnatisect leaves.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
